<h1 style="background-color:darkseagreen;">Spider poem</h1>

<img src="https://static.scientificamerican.com/sciam/cache/file/D8C5A8CB-5415-481E-96AF75FCA8AA5EA8_source.jpg?w=600">

<p style="background-color:lightseagreen;">
“She asks me to kill the spider.
Instead, I get the most
peaceful weapons I can find.



I take a cup and a napkin.
I catch the spider, put it outside
and allow it to walk away.



If I am ever caught in the wrong place
at the wrong time, just being alive
and not bothering anyone,



I hope I am greeted
with the same kind
of mercy.”


― Rudy Francisco, Helium

